FBIS3-60354 "jpten002__l94012" JPRS-TEN-94-002-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Environmental Issues 25 January 1994 EAST ASIA JAPAN Japan Environmental News Update (1-15 September 1993) Symposium on Environmental Protection 946C3801L Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 14 Sep 93 p 14--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY 946C3801L Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN Language: Japanese Article Type:CSO [Complete text of article obtained through NIKKEI BIZ DATABASE] [Text] The Environment Agency and the Japan Environment Association (director: Mutsumi Kato) will host "Symposium on Environmental Protection Vision" at the Tojo Kaikan on 30 September. It is intended to promote the interests of people concerned with important issues involving environmental policies, focused this time on the "Use of and Problems With Economic Measures." University professors and local government administrators will discuss the carbon tax, the deposit charge system and paid garbage collection. Attendance is free of charge.
